# Two people work this repo through git with different agents, so the shared
# records get edited simultaneously more than anything else. For the two that
# are pure append-per-line, take BOTH sides automatically rather than raising a
# conflict — losing someone's claim or changelog entry is worse than a duplicate
# line, which is visible and trivially tidied.
#
# Deliberately NOT applied to backlog.md or requirements-coverage.md: a clash
# there usually means two people changed the same item's status, and that
# genuinely needs a human to look.
COORD.md    merge=union
CHANGELOG.md merge=union
